'''pa*sha''', also pacha (pä’shə, păsh’ə, pə-shä’)
noun
#historical title of a high-ranking military or civil official in the Ottoman empire, who governed territories called pashaluks; ranked above [[beys]]; ranked below [[vizier|viziers]]
#honorary title, "Sir"

